dt %>%

    data = map_data(map = 'world'),

  stat_summary_2d(
    data = dt,

map <- ggplot(dt, aes(x = Longitude, y = Latitude, group = ID)) + 
  geom_polygon(
    data = map_data("world"), 
    aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group),

  geom_path(data = dt, aes(group = ID, colour = Wind.kt), size = 0.5) +

New Visualizations

Data Transformation (Pushing some variables to factor) Note that the Month is pushed to a factor that have a new level for each month. However, in our dataset we have no observations for February and march. When I introduce this level in the table it shows no data for those two months. There are no NAs in our data, the level function just shows that there is no data for that month.

df_temp = dt %>%
  mutate(
    Nature = factor(Nature),
    Season = factor(Season), # season is year not season.... 
    #Month = factor(Month),
    Month = factor(Month, levels = c(month.name)),
  )

df_temp %>%
  #arrange(match(Month, month.name)) %>% 
  select(Nature, Wind.kt, Latitude, Longitude,  Month ) %>% 
  tbl_summary(by =Nature ) %>%
  add_overall() %>% 
  modify_spanning_header(c("stat_1", "stat_2","stat_3","stat_4","stat_5") ~ "**Nature of the Hurricane**")
